HEADWORD: Overpay
<hw>O`ver*pay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overpaid</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overpaying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pay
too much to; to reward too highly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pay too much for; <as>as, to <ex>overpay</ex> the
loan balance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overpeer</ent>⟦br⟧
